## Recommended Refactored Hierarchy

Based on the analysis, here's a hierarchy that resolves all contradictions:

```mermaid
graph TD
    FDS["FrequencyDomainSolver"]
    
    subgraph "Single Solid"
        FDS -->|".fom (after solve)"| FOM["FOM: Z, S, eigenmodes"]
        FOM -->|".reduce(tol=...)"| MOR1["ModelOrderReduction"]
        MOR1 -->|".solve(fmin, fmax, n)"| MOR1
        MOR1 -->|".get_eigenvalues()"| EV1["eigenvalues"]
    end
    
    subgraph "Multi Solid"
        FDS -->|".foms (after solve, per_domain)"| FOMS["FOMCollection"]
        FOMS -->|".reduce(tol=...)"| ROMS["ROMCollection + shared MOR"]
        FOMS -->|".concatenate()"| FOMConcat["ConcatResult (FOM-level Z concat)"]
        ROMS -->|".concatenate()"| CS["ConcatenatedSystem"]
        CS -->|".solve(fmin, fmax, n)"| CS
        CS -->|".get_eigenvalues()"| EV2["eigenvalues"]
        FOMConcat -->|".reduce()"| MOR2["ModelOrderReduction"]
    end
```

**Key changes from current state:**
1. Replace `.rom` property with explicit `.reduce()` method on [FOMResult](file:///c:/Users/Soske/Documents/git_projects/cavsim3d/solvers/results.py#40-145) and [FOMCollection](file:///c:/Users/Soske/Documents/git_projects/cavsim3d/solvers/results.py#329-556)
2. Replace `.concat` property with explicit `.concatenate()` method
3. Remove [ROMResult](file:///c:/Users/Soske/Documents/git_projects/cavsim3d/solvers/results.py#151-218) as a top-level navigation node — users interact directly with [ModelOrderReduction](file:///c:/Users/Soske/Documents/git_projects/cavsim3d/rom/reduction.py#13-1027) and [ConcatenatedSystem](file:///c:/Users/Soske/Documents/git_projects/cavsim3d/solvers/concatenation.py#31-624)
4. Delete cascade method entirely
5. Add guards: `fds.fom.concatenate()` → warning; `fds.foms[i].reduce()` works per-solid
6. Keep FOM-level concatenation separate from ROM-level [ConcatenatedSystem](file:///c:/Users/Soske/Documents/git_projects/cavsim3d/solvers/concatenation.py#31-624) (option c above)

**What stays the same:**
- [ModelOrderReduction](file:///c:/Users/Soske/Documents/git_projects/cavsim3d/rom/reduction.py#13-1027) as the active ROM object with [reduce()](file:///c:/Users/Soske/Documents/git_projects/cavsim3d/rom/reduction.py#411-542), [solve()](file:///c:/Users/Soske/Documents/git_projects/cavsim3d/solvers/frequency_domain.py#650-797), [concatenate()](file:///c:/Users/Soske/Documents/git_projects/cavsim3d/rom/reduction.py#671-716)
- [ConcatenatedSystem](file:///c:/Users/Soske/Documents/git_projects/cavsim3d/solvers/concatenation.py#31-624) as the active coupled-ROM object with [couple()](file:///c:/Users/Soske/Documents/git_projects/cavsim3d/solvers/concatenation.py#294-348), [solve()](file:///c:/Users/Soske/Documents/git_projects/cavsim3d/solvers/frequency_domain.py#650-797)
- [EigenMixinBase](file:///c:/Users/Soske/Documents/git_projects/cavsim3d/solvers/eigen_mixin.py#18-807) for eigenvalue computation across all types
- [ReducedStructure](file:///c:/Users/Soske/Documents/git_projects/cavsim3d/rom/structures.py#8-108) as the data container for ROM→concatenation handoff
